/*
  # Reseed field_figures with correct DFS figure data

  This migration replaces ALL field_figures content with the authoritative
  DFS (Det frivillige Skyttervesen) standard figures. It uses INSERT ... ON CONFLICT
  to be safely idempotent: existing rows are fully updated, new rows are inserted.

  ## Problem
  Previous seed migrations contained autogenerated placeholder SVGs. The correct
  professional SVGs were applied via direct SQL but never captured in a migration.
  A database reset would revert to the wrong figures.

  ## What this migration does
  1. Marks ALL existing field_figures as inactive (is_active = false)
  2. Upserts all 31 correct DFS figures with professional SVGs, correct metadata,
     names, dimensions, distances, and sort orders
  3. The upsert ON CONFLICT(code) ensures existing rows (with FK references) keep
     their IDs, preserving match_holds and competition_stages references

  ## Figures included

  ### Grovfelt (21 figures, sort_order 100-520)
  - B45, B65, B100: Standing silhouette figures
  - C20, C25, C30, C35, C40, C50: Circle figures
  - Stripe-30/10, Stripe-13/40: Stripe figures
  - S-25H, S-25V: Slot/spalte figures
  - 1/8, 1/6, 1/4, 1/4V, 1/3: Fraction segment figures
  - Smaen, Sirkel, Tonne: Special figures

  ### Finfelt (10 figures, sort_order 1100-1190)
  - C15, Sirkel Finfelt, Tonne finfelt: Circle/barrel variants
  - Hjul, Prisme: Wheel and prism shapes
  - Mini-1/4, Mini-1/3, Minismaen: Mini variants
  - 1/10: Tenth segment
  - Stripe finfelt: Stripe variant

  ## Security
  - No RLS changes
  - No table structure changes
*/

-- Step 1: Mark all existing figures inactive. The upsert below will re-activate the correct ones.
UPDATE field_figures SET is_active = false WHERE is_active = true;

-- Step 2: Upsert all 31 correct DFS figures.
-- ON CONFLICT(code) preserves existing row IDs (and therefore FK references).

-- ============================================================
-- GROVFELT FIGURES
-- ============================================================

